        <span class="h5">How to avoid frozen and burst pipes.</span>
        <span class="h1 enlighten">Why do <b>frozen pipes sometimes burst?</b></span>
      </h2>
      <p slot="paragraph"><span style="color: red;">Please reduce content here</span></p>
      <p slot="paragraph">Water expands as it freezes, pressurising the pipe from the inside out.  Whether the pipe is strong enough to withstand the pressure without buckling comes down to the volume of water that’s frozen, the type, shape and age of the pipe, and whether corrosion was already present.</p>
      <p slot="paragraph">The good news is that with a few simple precautions, it’s often preventable – and definitely worth the time. The Association of British Insurers (ABI) estimates that the cost of insurance claims for a burst pipe can rise to around £7,500 during freezing weather.</p>
